2. METHODOLOGY: THE RECURRING PANIC MODEL (RPM)

The Institute proposes the following model:

Technological Panic Cycle (TPC):
	1.	New machine appears
	2.	Commentators declare it unprecedented
	3.	Commentators declare all jobs will disappear
	4.	Productivity increases
	5.	New jobs appear that sound fake
	6.	Society becomes richer
	7.	Repeat with new machine

This cycle has been repeating since approximately Fire v1.0.

We therefore introduce the core equation of technological panic:

Panic = (Speed of Machine × Media Attention) ÷ Historical Memory

Where Historical Memory is typically near zero.

