5. CONCLUSION

After extensive research, the Institute concludes that machines doing the work of many humans very quickly is not a new phenomenon, does not break economics, and has in fact been the main driver of rising living standards since the invention of tools, agriculture, and not dying at age 30.

However, despite this conclusion, the Institute simultaneously recommends immediate and total panic, as this time is clearly different, for reasons to be determined later.

